COSMOS FS2 (docs/COSMOS-FACET-SEAMS-DESIGN.md §3.2) — the FP_RADIAL_DATUM C++ mirror.

Applies AFTER 0008 (glob order), on the fully-patched VoxelGeneratorCosmos. Adds the per-column
datum shift S = round(solve |p0 + s*n_hat| = R), mirroring FacetAtlas.datum_shift EXACTLY from the
already-frozen facet_frame/off/r (zero new frozen data): resolve each cell at true y - S in
generate_block, +S headroom on both all-air bounds, and g + S skin heights in sample_columns.
Gated by the `radial_datum` config bool (plumbed from module_world + facet_skin_tier); returns 0
when off => byte-identical to the pre-FS2 engine. Kept as a standalone patch (not inline edits to
0007/0008) so the hunk offsets are git-generated and cannot drift against the earlier patches.

